resps:
The constraints determine all attributes except for Bob’s and Carol’s hobbies: the remaining hobbies, Dancing and Music, can be swapped between them without violating any clue.

One valid solution is:

Answer: {"Bob":{"HouseColor":"Purple","Pet":"Rabbit","Drink":"Soda","Job":"Teacher","Hobby":"Dancing"},"Frank":{"HouseColor":"Red","Pet":"Dog","Drink":"Juice","Job":"Nurse","Hobby":"Sports"},"Carol":{"HouseColor":"Yellow","Pet":"Hamster","Drink":"Water","Job":"Artist","Hobby":"Music"},"Alice":{"HouseColor":"Black","Pet":"Fish","Drink":"Smoothie","Job":"Doctor","Hobby":"Cooking"},"Iris":{"HouseColor":"White","Pet":"Turtle","Drink":"Milk","Job":"Pilot","Hobby":"Gaming"}}

Jack must be the Doctor, so Jack also has Milk, Sports, Purple house, and the Cat. Grace has the Green house, so Grace has Juice and must be the Artist; Grace also has the Bird. Alice drinks Smoothie, so Alice has the Black house and Reading hobby. Mike has the Turtle; since the Red house has the Hamster, Mike cannot be Red, so Mike is Orange, drinks Coffee, and is the Engineer. Emma is therefore Red, has the Hamster, drinks Soda, and has Dancing.

The constraints leave Alice/Emma’s remaining jobs and Grace/Mike’s remaining hobbies interchangeable; the JSON below is one valid completion.

Answer: {"Jack":{"HouseColor":"Purple","Pet":"Cat","Drink":"Milk","Job":"Doctor","Hobby":"Sports"},"Grace":{"HouseColor":"Green","Pet":"Bird","Drink":"Juice","Job":"Artist","Hobby":"Hiking"},"Alice":{"HouseColor":"Black","Pet":"Rabbit","Drink":"Smoothie","Job":"Pilot","Hobby":"Reading"},"Mike":{"HouseColor":"Orange","Pet":"Turtle","Drink":"Coffee","Job":"Engineer","Hobby":"Music"},"Emma":{"HouseColor":"Red","Pet":"Hamster","Drink":"Soda","Job":"Nurse","Hobby":"Dancing"}}
